**File:** `src/app/api/auth/login/route.ts`

```typescript
const loginAttempts = new Map<string, { count: number; resetTime: number }>();
```

**Problem:** Entries survive for 15 minutes but the Map grows unbounded by unique IPs. Thousands of unique IPs = memory leak.

**Fix ‚Äî cleanup expired entries periodically or use a TTL Map:**
```typescript
function cleanupExpired() {
  const now = Date.now();
  for (const [ip, entry] of loginAttempts) {
    if (now > entry.resetTime) loginAttempts.delete(ip);
  }
}
setInterval(cleanupExpired, 60_000); // every minute
```
Or just use a proper external rate limiter.

